    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-04T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="628"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.203/220: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-04T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 4 [<hi rend="italic">10</hi>], 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>210. Your 169, January 30. Department agrees to suggested amendment. Department
                    has no objection to either form of additional paragraph concerning reciprocity
                    but prefers shorter form.</p>
                <p>You are authorized to exchange notes on basis of this telegram and Department’s
                    No. 18, January 4, as soon as the Treaty of January 11<note n="7"
                        xml:id="d628fn7">Signed at Washington; it provided for relinquishment of
                        extraterritorial rights in China and the regulation of related matters, 57
                        Stat. 767.</note> becomes effective.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
